h-end tailoring market and not being subtle about it at all.<br>
Prices on any items are being drastically undercut, and it he's matched, undercut again. The profit in producing said items is just plummeting.<br>
But here's another thing.<br>
This person is GROSSLY ramping up prices on high-end supplies. Like, in some cases 4X going rate or more. Don't buy from him then, you say? Not quite that easy. What happens is, unfamiliar_loothaver_01 comes in with Storm Rider Blood and doesn't know how to price it. He checks and sees Robynhood has some at 4k. So he lists his at 3.5k, thinking he's offering a good price. But Storm Rider Blood has traditionally gone for 1k until Robyn's recent antics. So now ANOTHER person comes in and sees THOSE two prices and matches 3.5k. Soon it's up across the board and suddenly an item has quadrupled in price in the bazaar. What Robynhood is effectively doing is locking out aspiring tailors who need to buy any high-end supplies. I am seeing this tactic work with item after item.<br>
So this combination of drastic undercuts on finished prices to bone established tailors AND escalating prices on raw goods to bone up-and-coming tailors is just trashing the tailoring market. Except, of course, for Robynhood. Competition is one thing, but this is a blatant and malicious attempt to utterly dominate a fairly expensive and difficult trade. I worked hard to get to GM level stuff and now it looks as though I cannot sell a single piece because of this player's actions unless I totally lowball HIM, at which point my profit is destroyed and there's no point in having done it at all.<br>
<br>
